  "title": "Forklift Operator",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will operate forklifts to move, load, and unload materials safely and efficiently in the warehouse. You will also inspect equipment, organize products, maintain safety standards, and support general warehouse tasks as needed.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Operate forklifts and other material-handling equipment following safety procedures to move goods within the warehouse</li><li>Load and unload materials accurately to ensure timely processing and storage</li><li>Stack and store products in designated warehouse locations to maintain order and accessibility</li><li>Inspect forklifts before each use and report any mechanical issues to ensure safe operation</li><li>Maintain a clean and organized work area to support safety and efficiency</li><li>Follow all safety rules and company policies to prevent accidents and maintain compliance</li><li>Assist with general warehouse duties such as inventory handling and order preparation when required</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Hold a valid forklift operator license/certification to operate equipment legally and safely</li><li>Demonstrate knowledge of warehouse safety procedures to minimize risks during operations</li><li>Ability to lift heavy items and stand for extended periods to perform physical warehouse tasks safely</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Previous experience working in warehouse or logistics environments to enhance operational effectiveness</li><li>Basic knowledge of inventory management to support stock control and accuracy</li></ul><p><strong>Other Information</strong></p><ul><li>Working hours: 7:30am to 7:30pm</li></ul>",
